According to the city some places could experience unplanned water cuts due to high consumption rates. JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg Water says that although the majority of residents have been using water sparingly, levels at a number of reservoirs are still alarmingly low.According to the city, some places could experience unplanned water cuts due to high consumption rates.Residents are currently under level 2 restrictions.Joburg Water s Tidimalo Chuene says residents should expect to see more Johannesburg Metropolitan Police Department officers patrolling in high consumption areas. Please just be considerate that when you use too much water, areas in high lying regions are likely to suffer and that is the biggest message. We are monitoring them around the clock. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)